-- Bank St. Petersburg CEO Savelyev Injured in Helicopter Accident
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-04-08T11:40:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/bank-st-petersburg-ceo-savelyev-injured-in-helicopter-accident.html
Alexander Savelyev, chief executive
officer of Bank Saint Petersburg, was sent to hospital after a
helicopter he was riding in made an emergency landing because of
adverse weather conditions, according to a  statement  posted on
the lender’s website yesterday.  Savelyev’s condition is “not severe,” according to the
statement. First Deputy Chairman Vladislav Guz will act as his
replacement while he recovers, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
